    ThrowingPredicate1<T1>

    @InheritOnly
public interface AbstractThrowingPredicate1<T1,H extends AbstractThrowingPredicate1.Handler<T1>,P extends AbstractThrowingPredicate1<T1,H,P>>
extends AbstractThrowingPredicateN<H,P>, net.ashwork.functionality.partial.InputChainableInput<T1>, net.ashwork.functionality.partial.FunctionVariant<java.lang.Boolean,AbstractThrowingToBooleanFunction1<T1,?>>
    Represents a predicate that accepts one argument and produces a boolean-valued result or throws a throwable. This is the one-arity specialization for AbstractThrowingPredicateN. This is the predicate specialization for AbstractThrowingToBooleanFunction1. This is the throwing variation of AbstractPredicate1.
    Since:
    1.0.0
    See Also:
    AbstractThrowingPredicateN, AbstractThrowingToBooleanFunction1, AbstractPredicate1
    API Note:
    This is an abstract predicate and should not be used directly. It should instead be called by one of its subtypes.
